HEADWORD: Dissuasive
<hw>Dis*sua"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tending to
dissuade or divert from a measure or purpose; dehortatory; <as>as,
<ex>dissuasive</ex> advice</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A
dissuasive argument or counsel; dissuasion; dehortation.</def>
<au>Prynne.</au></def2> -- <wordforms><wf>Dis*sua"sive*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
